Furthermore, a good linear relationship between quenching ratio (F/F0
                           ) and water content from 0 % to 50 % was shown in Fig. 6(a–d), the linear correlation coefficient was 0.9956–0.9970 in each solvent system. The LOD was calculated according to the equation based on International Union of Pure and Applied Chemistry (3δ/k, n = 10). LODs of water were 0.71 %, 0.80 %, 1.82 % and 0.46 % for DMF, EtOH, MeOH and ACN, respectively. It is noteworthy that with each 20 % increment in water content, the color of the LCOF-DT suspension solution in the four organic solvent system progressively darkened (Fig. 7
                           ). This observable color change in response to varying water content could be utilized for rapid and on-site detection in real sample analyses.
